properties.areaDesc: Waters from Bonita Beach to Englewood FL out 20 to 60 NM; Coastal waters from Englewood to Tarpon Springs FL out 20 NM
properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 6 at 3:52AM EST until February 7 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 25 to 30 kt with gusts
up over 45 kt and seas 10 to 12 feet expected. For the Small
Craft Advisory, south winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt
and seas 7 to 10 feet.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Englewood to Tarpon Springs FL out
20 NM and Waters from Bonita Beach to Englewood FL out 20 to
60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 1 PM this afternoon to 1 AM
EST Friday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 AM to 10 AM
EST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 1 AM EST FRIDAY... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 10 AM EST FRIDAY
